<article>
    <h1>&#x2018;HEART AT&#xAD;TACK&#x2019; FRIED RICE</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201115/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-11-15"><time>2020-11-15</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | FOOD &amp; DRINK</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>What: Sold with New Ubin Seafood’s USDA Black An­gus “Choice” Rib­eye (from $82.50), this ver­sion of “heart at­tack” fried rice is cooked with beef drip­pings from the rib­eye steak.</p>
    <p>The rice is fried in the oil, along with dark soya sauce, oys­ter sauce and Sarawak white pep­per, while the crisp bits of fat are used as gar­nish.</p>
    <p>It is a must-or­der dish when din­ing at the zichar es­tab­lish­ment, which sells up to 30 por­tions a day and about 440 por­tions a month.</p>
    <p>Where: New Ubin Seafood out­lets at 02-01B/C Chi­jmes, 30 Vic­to­ria Street; 18 Tampines In­dus­trial Cres­cent, 01-16; and Ra­mada by Wyn­d­ham Sin­ga­pore at Zhong­shan Park, 18 Ah Hood Road; var­i­ous open­ing hours</p>
    <p>Info: Call 9740-6870, or­der at or­der.newu­bin­seafood.com or go to newu­bin­seafood.com</p>

